review_text: Ok how can I start? This is an ok Option if youre a beginner gardener and if youre in a budget, but OUTDOORS. This is a potting mix thats mainly peat moss and bark. If youre using this in Houseplants for indoors, PLEASE add more perlite to it or else your soil will stay moist for even a month and attract fingus gnats or even rot your plants. i May even reccomend you add some bark or mulch to it for outside purposes to maake it more well draining. Again if youre  a  Beginner youre just growing some herbs and pretty annual flowers in pots, its an ok option for you to use. what I dont like about this mix which is also what i dont like about pretty much most of commercial potting mixes available on the market is that it has PEAT MOSS. If yall dont know, peat moss takes Hundreds of years to form and its mined faster than it grows. Peat moss mining is responsible for wetland destruction and also the release of carbon dioxide into the Atmosphere meaning its not eco-friendly. I wish that instead of Peat moss they would use something more sustainable like coconut coir or just compost and the grinded  forest products that already hold on to moisture. Thats the only thing i say its a bad thing about this brand. The quality and price are good and if no you add more stuff to it like more bark and more fertilizer, a 1 cubic foot bag csn last you a long time. If yall complain about not "Not Having soil" remember that soil is a blend of organic matter like decomposed and decomposing animals, manure and plant matter and inorganic matter like clay sand and volcanic stone. Another thing I want to say about it is that the name Clearly says it all. Its a potting MIX not SOIL

product_name: Expert Gardener Indoor and Outdoor Potting Soil Mix, 2 cu. ft. Bag
review_text: Ok how can I start? This is an ok Option if youre a beginner gardener and if youre in a budget, but OUTDOORS. This is a potting mix thats mainly peat moss and bark. If youre using this in Houseplants for indoors, PLEASE add more perlite to it or else your soil will stay moist for even a month and attract fingus gnats or even rot your plants. i May even reccomend you add some bark or mulch to it for outside purposes to maake it more well draining. Again if youre  a  Beginner youre just growing some herbs and pretty annual flowers in pots, its an ok option for you to use. what I dont like about this mix which is also what i dont like about pretty much most of commercial potting mixes available on the market is that it has PEAT MOSS. If yall dont know, peat moss takes Hundreds of years to form and its mined faster than it grows. Peat moss mining is responsible for wetland destruction and also the release of carbon dioxide into the Atmosphere meaning its not eco-friendly. I wish that instead of Peat moss they would use something more sustainable like coconut coir or just compost and the grinded  forest products that already hold on to moisture. Thats the only thing i say its a bad thing about this brand. The quality and price are good and if no you add more stuff to it like more bark and more fertilizer, a 1 cubic foot bag csn last you a long time. If yall complain about not "Not Having soil" remember that soil is a blend of organic matter like decomposed and decomposing animals, manure and plant matter and inorganic matter like clay sand and volcanic stone. Another thing I want to say about it is that the name Clearly says it all. Its a potting MIX not SOIL
review_lower: ok how can i start? this is an ok option if youre a beginner gardener and if youre in a budget, but outdoors. this is a potting mix thats mainly peat moss and bark. if youre using this in houseplants for indoors, please add more perlite to it or else your soil will stay moist for even a month and attract fingus gnats or even rot your plants. i may even reccomend you add some bark or mulch to it for outside purposes to maake it more well draining. again if youre  a  beginner youre just growing some herbs and pretty annual flowers in pots, its an ok option for you to use. what i dont like about this mix which is also what i dont like about pretty much most of commercial potting mixes available on the market is that it has peat moss. if yall dont know, peat moss takes hundreds of years to form and its mined faster than it grows. peat moss mining is responsible for wetland destruction and also the release of carbon dioxide into the atmosphere meaning its not eco-friendly. i wish that instead of peat moss they would use something more sustainable like coconut coir or just compost and the grinded  forest products that already hold on to moisture. thats the only thing i say its a bad thing about this brand. the quality and price are good and if no you add more stuff to it like more bark and more fertilizer, a 1 cubic foot bag csn last you a long time. if yall complain about not "not having soil" remember that soil is a blend of organic matter like decomposed and decomposing animals, manure and plant matter and inorganic matter like clay sand and volcanic stone. another thing i want to say about it is that the name clearly says it all. its a potting mix not soil
